                                                        <h3>Introduction</h3>
        <div id="book-description" class="u-content u-overflow-wrap"><p>This handbook covers a wealth of topics from number theory, special attention being given to estimates and inequalities. As a rule, the most important results are presented, together with their refinements, extensions or generalisations. These may be applied to other aspects of number theory, or to a wide range of mathematical disciplines. Cross-references provide new insight into fundamental research. </p>
<p><em>Audience:</em> This is an indispensable reference work for specialists in number theory and other mathematicians who need access to some of these results in their own fields of research.</p></div>
